c:$
role: dev
task: S04-T4
title: Tactical accents and operational feel
gate: OPEN
stack_source: @incoming/requirements.md
stack: [TypeScript, React, MobX, Material UI]
requires: [UI]

objective: |
  Add subtle tactical accents: optional pulse/glow for live data, focus borders,
  and an "operational" polish that completes the generals WOW effect.

context:
  - S03 glass variants (glass-glow, glass-neon) support emphasis; use sparingly for live/critical state.
  - Motion must be subtle and purposeful (e.g. status indicator, not decorative).

steps:
  1. Define or reuse accent patterns for "live" or "critical" state (e.g. soft pulse, border glow).
  2. Apply to key status indicators or real-time data points only; avoid overuse.
  3. Ensure focus states (keyboard/a11y) use visible border or outline per design system.
  4. Optionally add a single "operational" detail (e.g. subtle grid or line accent) to main layout.

acceptance-criteria:
  - Live/critical states are visually distinct without being distracting.
  - Focus and interaction states are clear and accessible.
  - Overall feel is "operational" and premium, aligned with glass + dark theme.
